statements.sql: select `A`.`id`, `A`.`parent`, `B`.`title` from `categories` as `A` left join `category_languages` as `B` on `A`.`id` = `B`.`category_id` where (A.type = 'thue-xe' or A.type = 'default') and `B`.`language` = 'vi' order by `A`.`priority` asc, `A`.`id` desc

select count(*) as aggregate from `products` as `A` left join `product_languages` as `B` on `A`.`id` = `B`.`product_id` left join `category_languages` as `C` on `A`.`category_id` = `C`.`category_id` where A.type='thue-xe' and `B`.`language` = 'vi' and `C`.`language` = 'vi'

select `A`.*, `B`.`title`, `C`.`title` as `category` from `products` as `A` left join `product_languages` as `B` on `A`.`id` = `B`.`product_id` left join `category_languages` as `C` on `A`.`category_id` = `C`.`category_id` where A.type='thue-xe' and `B`.`language` = 'vi' and `C`.`language` = 'vi' order by `A`.`user_id` desc, `A`.`priority` asc, `A`.`id` desc limit 25 offset 0
